revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== {{suffix|en|xenomorphous|ly}} ===Adverb=== {{en-adv}} # {{lb|en|petrography|of a mineral grain}} In a [[xenomorphous]] manner. #* '''1991''', Sidney Mindess, National Institute of Standards and Technology (U.S.), American Ceramic Society, [https://books.google.com/books?id=xsdRAAAAMAAJ&q=%22xenomorphously%22&dq=%22xenomorphously%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjkiuvp3aPWAhXpxlQKHbzoDHQQ6AEIKDAA Advances in cementitious materials] #*: Alite may be '''xenomorphously''' or hypidimorphously shaped, with the grain sizes of the alite crystals varying between 0.010 to 0.030 mm.
